DEVELOPMENT APPROVAL (PENDING) FOR A 161 ROOM 3.5 STAR HOTEL WITH ESPLANADE FRONTAGE

A true piece of Cairns history, perfectly positioned on the business section of the Cairns Esplanade.

• 1,886sqm* with 2 street access
• Currently operating as a Motel / Hostel with 6 Esplanade Retail tenants and 1 Abbott Street retailer
• Approximately 135 beds in total
• DA pending for 161 room 3.5 star Hotel
• Directly opposite the Esplanade Lagoon / Parklands
• Good holding income

FOR SALE BY EXPRESSION OF INTEREST CLOSING WEDNESDAY 9TH NOVEMBER AT 5PM

A QUEENSLAND INSTITUTION

- Landmark Queensland Hotel situated in Cairns Central Business District as part of a high profile 7,076sqm* site.
- 1,335sqm* trading footprint with favourable 3am Liquor Licence and 35 Gaming Gaming Machine Authorities.
- High vaulted ceilings in the main bar with never to be replaced heritage features, making it a truly unique hotel.
- Commanding beer garden with large projector screen utilised for broadcasting most major sporting events.
- 'Breakaway' area allowing flexibility for function and conference space.
- Consistent revenue streams and balanced trade mix, presenting a solid base to further grow revenue across all
departments.
- Located opposite the Woolworths anchored Orchid Plaza Shopping Centre and within close proximity to the
foreshore & pier, Reef Casino and numerous accommodation hotels and backpackers.
- Current substantial Development Approval to reconfigure the hotel and beer garden, which affords the incoming
operator the ability to maximise the trading performance across all revenue streams.
- Cairns Courthouse Hotel is currently owned and operated remotely ensuring immediate upside by hands-on
operations from an owner operator.

For Sale by Expression of Interest closing Wednesday 13th July 2016 at 12:00pm (AEST).
